"title": "8209: commitment, to Jesus Christ",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8209",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Commitment to Jesus Christ is grounded in the knowledge of his saving power and divinity, and expresses itself in adoration and obedience to Jesus Christ.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ commanded people to make the commitment to follow him</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:19\">MAT 4:19</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:17\">MRK 1:17</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:9\">MAT 9:9</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:14\">MRK 2:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:27\">LUK 5:27</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:21-Matt19:22\">MAT 19:21–19:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:43\">JHN 1:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:19\">JHN 21:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:22\">JHN 21:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:5\">ROM 15:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:12\">1CO 1:12</a> <em>There may have been a “Christ-party” at Corinth, or in contrast with the sectarianism, Paul may be asserting his own commitment to Jesus Christ.</em></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ frequently spelt out the cost of commitment to him</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:37-Matt10:38\">MAT 10:37–10:38</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:26-Luke14:27\">LUK 14:26–14:27</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:24\">MAT 16:24</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:34\">MRK 8:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:23\">LUK 9:23</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:25-John12:26\">JHN 12:25–12:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:22\">MAT 8:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:39\">MAT 10:39</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:35\">MRK 8:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:33\">LUK 17:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:21\">MAT 19:21</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:21\">MRK 10:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:22\">LUK 18:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:28-Luke14:33\">LUK 14:28–14:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:21\">1PE 2:21</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's demand for commitment was sometimes met with a refusal</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:59\">LUK 9:59</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:61\">LUK 9:61</a></p>\n<h2>Sometimes people followed Jesus Christ without being truly committed to him</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:2\">JHN 6:2</a></strong> <em>This would have been true for many in the crowds.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:66\">JHN 6:66</a></p>\n<h2>Some committed themselves wholeheartedly to his invitation</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:20\">MAT 4:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:18\">MRK 1:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:22\">MAT 4:22</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:20\">MRK 1:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:9\">MAT 9:9</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:14\">MRK 2:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:28\">LUK 5:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:40\">JHN 1:40</a></p>\n<h2>Secret commitment to Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:42\">JHN 12:42</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:1-John3:2\">JHN 3:1–3:2</a></p>\n<h2>True commitment to Jesus Christ is seen in love and obedience to him</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:21\">JHN 14:21</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:12\">PHP 2:12</a></strong> <em>In response to who Jesus Christ is and what he has done.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:31\">JHN 8:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:15\">JHN 14:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:23-John14:24\">JHN 14:23–14:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:1\">1CO 11:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:22\">1CO 16:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:5-Eph6:6\">EPH 6:5–6:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:24\">EPH 6:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:3\">1JN 2:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:22-1John3:24\">1JN 3:22–3:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:4\">REV 14:4</a></p>",
